1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,921
[stirring music playing]

2
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:11,761
[clamoring]

3
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:13,388
[Mia] <i>Where is Datu Rahman?! Where is he?</i>

4
00:00:14,055 --> 00:00:15,306
<i>Where is Datu Rahman?!</i>

5
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:17,517
[Marcus] <i>If I’m right,</i>

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,436
<i>they didn’t move</i>
<i>Datu Rahman for his safety,</i>

7
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:21,438
<i>they’re planning to kill him.</i>

8
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:23,606
- [grunting, groaning]
- [Jalil] <i>Who are you?!</i>

9
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:24,816
[grunting, groaning]

10
00:00:24,899 --> 00:00:26,818
- Jalil!
- [electric zapping]

11
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:29,320
[Jalil] Father!

12
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:32,741
- [grunting]
- Let me go!

13
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:35,660
- [Jalil] Father!
- [tires screech]

14
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:38,872
[gunshots]

15
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:40,331
[Jalil] Father!

16
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:42,917
- [tires screech]
- [panting]

17
00:00:43,793 --> 00:00:45,962
[Marcus] <i>Lara! I saw the people</i>
<i>who took Datu Rahman.</i>

18
00:00:46,045 --> 00:00:47,338
<i>They were all wearing masks!</i>

19
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,466
<i>I crossed paths with them,</i>
<i>but they had guns.</i>

20
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:51,801
<i>Someone was running</i>
<i>after Datu Rahman's captors.</i>

21
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:52,886
<i>A man.</i>

22
00:00:53,386 --> 00:00:55,013
- Have you identified him?
- No.

23
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:57,390
[Marcus] <i>They're always</i>
<i>one step ahead of us.</i>

24
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:58,725
<i>They're going to kill Datu Rahman,</i>

25
00:00:58,808 --> 00:01:00,518
<i>and once he's gone,</i>
<i>the truth dies with him.</i>

26
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:01,978
[Lara] <i>If Dir. Azuelo finds out</i>
<i>about this,</i>

27
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,355
<i>you'll be terminated</i>
<i>from service without question.</i>

28
00:01:04,439 --> 00:01:06,232
[Marcus] <i>I don't care anymore, Lara.</i>

29
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,193
<i>Right now, I need to do the right thing.</i>

30
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:11,362
Is Marcus Reyes involved
in your father’s abduction?

31
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:12,322
[Jalil] <i>I don't know!</i>

32
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:14,574
<i>All I know is, the longer</i>
<i>Father remains missing,</i>

33
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,451
<i>the more danger he’ll be in.</i>

34
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,161
<i>The situation is very dangerous, Jamilah!</i>

35
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:21,498
That's why I'm here. To help you.

36
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:24,584
[Jamilah] <i>You weren't</i>
<i>the only one who lost family.</i>

37
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:25,877
<i>Me too!</i>

38
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:27,837
You are such a screw-up!

39
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,465
I didn't let Datu Rahman escape.

40
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:32,509
[Sabdani] <i>I was transferring him</i>
<i>to another vehicle, as ordered.</i>

41
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:34,844
[Montes] <i>You Muslims are all the same.</i>

42
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:38,056
<i>You're already causing trouble</i>
<i>after the mess you made!</i>

43
00:01:38,139 --> 00:01:39,641
[Azuelo] <i>Based on our investigation,</i>

44
00:01:39,724 --> 00:01:45,021
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar incited a riot</i>

45
00:01:45,104 --> 00:01:46,856
<i>in order to escape from the law.</i>

46
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,274
Liar.

47
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:52,362
Criminals like Datu Rahman
deserve to be shot down.

48
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:53,488
Domingo!

49
00:01:53,571 --> 00:01:56,199
I want a world free of crime.

50
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:58,910
[Felix] <i>Free of violence. That's all.</i>

51
00:01:59,828 --> 00:02:01,412
[Marcus] <i>Sir, why did you</i>
<i>tell that to the media?</i>

52
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,207
[Azuelo] <i>What were you doing there?</i>
<i>You're still suspended.</i>

53
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:07,836
[Marcus] <i>I want justice</i>
<i>for my comrades who lost their lives.</i>

54
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,003
<i>Sir, they were your men, too.</i>

55
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,213
Or were you part of their deaths?

56
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,006
- How dare you!
- Alright, sir.

57
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:13,967
[Marcus] <i>I'll uncover</i>
<i>the truth eventually.</i>

58
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:18,680
[mysterious theme music playing]

59
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:33,903
[gloomy music playing]

60
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,293
[fire sizzling]

61
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:56,175
[gloomy music continues]

62
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,721
[women on PA system] <i>Code blue!</i>
<i>Code blue! Calling Dr. Daileg.</i>

63
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:01,598
<i>Please proceed to Room 203.</i>
<i>Patient Patrick Marquez.</i>

64
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:05,018
[doctor] <i>Patient SPO3 Patrick Marquez.</i>
<i>Official time of death,</i>

65
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,270
<i>4:32 p.m.</i>

66
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,689
[doctor] <i>Clear.</i>

67
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:11,608
- [doctor] <i>Everybody clear.</i>
- [nurse] <i>Clear!</i>

68
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:15,320
[ECG monitor beeping]

69
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:18,907
- [grunts]
- [flesh squelches]

70
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:21,868
Oliver! Nurse!

71
00:03:22,452 --> 00:03:24,996
[Marcus] <i>Nurse! Help!</i>

72
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:27,624
[sighs]

73
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:35,131
ARREST OF DATU RAHMAN
ENDS IN MASSACRE

74
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:37,133
[rapid gunfire]

75
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,760
[Marcus] <i>The mission is compromised!</i>

76
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,846
<i>I repeat, the mission is compromised!</i>

77
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,599
[grim music playing]

78
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:55,026
[grim music continues]

79
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:16,464
[grim music continues]

80
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:21,052
[Gonzalez] <i>Are you sure about that?</i>

81
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:23,179
Who are you saying did it?

82
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:27,183
How dare accuse your fellow officers.

83
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,478
[grim music continues]

84
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:54,669
[Marcus] <i>Our mission to arrest</i>
<i>Datu Rahman on that island</i>

85
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:56,838
<i>was doomed from the start.</i>

86
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:00,425
<i>Someone’s orchestrating all of this.</i>

87
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,720
<i>I need to find out who.</i>

88
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,018
[music turns unsettling]

89
00:05:21,362 --> 00:05:22,697
[vehicles honking]

90
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:26,326
[suspenseful music playing]

91
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:38,004
[music swells]

92
00:05:43,384 --> 00:05:44,218
Brother!

93
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:47,096
Brother!

94
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,519
You know, I’ve had
a lot of respect for you

95
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:55,104
ever since our days in the Academy.

96
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,899
You’re not only a great cop,
but also a noble one.

97
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,988
If I’m truly great and noble,

98
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:08,910
why am I still stuck at SPO1?

99
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:12,205
I even got outpaced
by someone more junior than me.

100
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:16,501
And now that Datu Rahman escaped…

101
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:18,753
I'm being blamed for it.

102
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:23,049
People think that
because we're both Muslims,

103
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:25,426
we're both criminals.

104
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:29,222
Datu Rahman is a Tausug.

105
00:06:29,305 --> 00:06:30,890
I'm a Maranao.

106
00:06:31,432 --> 00:06:35,103
[pensive music playing]

107
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:36,687
What exactly happened?

108
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:39,941
I have no idea, brother.

109
00:06:40,024 --> 00:06:42,151
I held Datu Rahman tightly.

110
00:06:43,569 --> 00:06:46,030
But when the crowd swarmed us,

111
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,573
he slipped away.

112
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:48,908
He escaped.

113
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,035
But I'm sure…

114
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:52,912
he didn't do it alone.

115
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:55,248
Someone helped him escape.

116
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:57,542
Yes.

117
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:02,171
Someone did help him escape.

118
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,757
[tense music playing]

119
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,426
Before he was abducted.

120
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,179
Are you sure about that?

121
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:12,890
Yes.

122
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:15,351
[inhales, sighs]

123
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,979
I even went after his kidnappers.

124
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:22,275
[man] <i>Shoot Marcus Reyes!</i>

125
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:23,734
[rapid gunfire]

126
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:25,153
But they started shooting.

127
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:27,989
[tense music continues]

128
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:33,536
Here.

129
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:36,664
[Marcus] <i>I recovered this at the location.</i>

130
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:40,418
[stirring music playing]

131
00:08:01,105 --> 00:08:04,942
Everyone is blaming me

132
00:08:05,526 --> 00:08:07,445
for Datu Rahman's escape.

133
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,615
But I'll prove to them that I'm innocent.

134
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:14,952
Brother, while your suspension
is still in effect,

135
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:20,374
I’ll check NLEA’s ballistics data
for a match to this bullet.

136
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:25,588
Thank you, brother.

137
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:30,843
Don't tell anyone about this.

138
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,762
Let's keep this between us.

139
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:35,848
Even Agent Angeles?

140
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:38,601
Aren't you guys friends?

141
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:43,189
[music turns tense]

142
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,826
- [music fades]
- [traffic noise]

143
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:59,664
[somber music playing]

144
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:02,416
[grunting] Agh! Agh!

145
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:06,587
[sinister music]

146
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,266
[chairs thud]

147
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:20,059
- [Jalil] Let me go!
- [grunts]

148
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:22,186
[grunting and groaning]

149
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,813
[Jalil] Let me go!

150
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,526
[Jalil grunts]

151
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:36,075
What do they need from us?

152
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:42,164
Where did they take you, Father?

153
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,961
[somber music continues]

154
00:09:53,801 --> 00:09:59,432
[foreboding music playing]

155
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,566
[line ringing]

156
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:09,859
Uncle.

157
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:14,280
Do you know anyone who can help us access

158
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:16,407
the CCTV around here?

159
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:19,285
[foreboding music continues]

160
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:27,418
[pensive music playing]

161
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,129
[indistinct chattering]

162
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:33,841
[radio beeps]

163
00:10:35,509 --> 00:10:36,552
[sighs]

164
00:10:39,096 --> 00:10:40,222
[sighs exasperatedly]

165
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,058
It's you again.

166
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:44,852
Tell me, when will I be free from you?

167
00:10:44,935 --> 00:10:46,354
I'll tell you when.

168
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:49,607
Hold on. Aren't you suspended?

169
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,859
Dennis, even though I'm suspended,

170
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:54,445
you can't forget what I have against you.

171
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:58,949
I might need to remind you
what I have on my phone here.

172
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:01,243
- Fine, fine. Alright.
- What?

173
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:02,828
What do you need?

174
00:11:03,579 --> 00:11:05,414
That's what I like about you.

175
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:07,375
You've always been easy to talk to.

176
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,005
Come in.

177
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:16,175
Sorry for the trouble.

178
00:11:16,258 --> 00:11:18,511
Oh, please. Don't sweat it.

179
00:11:18,594 --> 00:11:21,764
I can't possibly say no to Uncle Omar.

180
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:24,475
Besides… [scoffs]

181
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:25,935
…this one's easy peasy.

182
00:11:27,269 --> 00:11:28,270
[exhales]

183
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,523
[keyboard clacking]

184
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:34,193
[tense music]

185
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:41,575
[Marcus] <i>Where are you taking Datu Rahman?</i>

186
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:47,498
[keyboard clacking]

187
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:49,083
[digital trilling]

188
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:53,003
[digital trilling]

189
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:55,506
[keyboard clacking]

190
00:11:55,589 --> 00:11:58,843
[tense music playing]

191
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:10,938
Why did it disappear?

192
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,356
It just disappeared.

193
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:14,483
[Marcus] How did that happen?

194
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:17,111
Why didn't they appear
on the other monitors?

195
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:18,571
Hold on.

196
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:19,780
Where did they go?

197
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:24,326
When they reached Olivios Street,

198
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:25,578
they disappeared.

199
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:32,418
There are other commercial properties
on that street.

200
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:35,838
But mostly, it is residential.

201
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:39,508
They may have taken Datu there.

202
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:40,634
You know what?

203
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:43,095
Maybe what you're looking
for is in Olivios Street.

204
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:44,388
No.

205
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:46,390
No. Something's wrong.

206
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,727
[Dennis] I don't think
it's in Del Puente Street.

207
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:52,771
We've been here for a while.
We're going round in circles.

208
00:12:54,565 --> 00:12:56,859
Hold on, hold on. Pause it.

209
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,404
Zoom it.

210
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,450
That car…

211
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,870
I've been seeing it for a while.

212
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:09,622
Which one?

213
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,001
- There!
- [keyboard clacks]

214
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,294
- That one.
- This one?

215
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:19,715
I've been seeing it because…

216
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:23,010
the video is on a loop.

217
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:26,597
The footage was looped,
so we can't track them down.

218
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:30,601
[tense music continues]

219
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,657
[music fades]

220
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:47,618
[suspenseful music continues]

221
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:50,496
- [chair thuds]
- [Jamilah] Brother Jalil…

222
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,832
Jamilah, enough already.

223
00:13:54,416 --> 00:13:55,376
Enough already.

224
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:57,503
Brother Jalil, you know me.

225
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:59,171
If you forbid me from helping,

226
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:01,674
I'll look for Father myself.

227
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,635
Are you threatening me?

228
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:06,679
No.

229
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:10,641
I'm just telling you.

230
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:17,606
[Omar] You both want the same thing.

231
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,483
To find your father.

232
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,151
Why don't you just work together

233
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:23,153
to speed up the search?

234
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:29,618
[sighs] Do you think
they took Father there?

235
00:14:30,202 --> 00:14:31,704
[tense music]

236
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:36,292
Mm-hmm.

237
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:41,046
If I'm right,

238
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:45,301
we'll find Father somewhere here.

239
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,645
[suspenseful music continues]

240
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:18,417
It's this road right here.

241
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:22,338
[keyboard clacking]

242
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:30,888
This one.

243
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:32,556
It's right here.

244
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:34,892
And this one.

245
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:37,019
It's right here.

246
00:15:37,853 --> 00:15:39,605
Then this last road.

247
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:41,106
It's here.

248
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:47,237
[keyboard clacking]

249
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,827
[Jalil] This area right here

250
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:57,373
is where the red car kept appearing.

251
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,086
I can't be mistaken.

252
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,631
[tense music]

253
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:19,019
I'm sure of it.

254
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:22,272
I can't be wrong.

255
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:33,534
[suspenseful music continues]

256
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:55,222
[suspenseful music continues]

257
00:17:04,773 --> 00:17:07,776
[tense music playing]

258
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:17,494
[car approaching, tires screech]

259
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:21,749
[tense music]

260
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:15,094
[thuds]

261
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:33,862
[tense music continues]

262
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:58,011
[Lara] <i>Marcus, I'll let you come,</i>
<i>but not as SID.</i>

263
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,012
<i>Just an observer.</i>

264
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:02,808
[Jalil] Allah, I'm seeking your help.

265
00:19:02,891 --> 00:19:06,937
[Jalil speaking in Tausug]

266
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:09,439
‪[tense music playing]

267
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,153
Angeles, why is Reyes there?

268
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,946
[Azuelo] <i>He's suspended!</i>

269
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:21,160
[grunting and groaning]

270
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,662
[grunting and groaning]

271
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,126
You?!

272
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:33,297
- Don't try to run or I'll shoot you!
- [gunshot]

273
00:19:34,339 --> 00:19:35,465
[gunshots]

274
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:37,885
- Stop! You might shoot Marcus.
- Stop it!

275
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:40,721
Go around the area!

276
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,807
- [gunshots]
- [body thuds]

277
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:46,518
- Enough! Enough!
- Stop it!

278
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,395
That bastard is a criminal!

279
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,521
We need to catch him alive.

280
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:53,442
[gunshots]

281
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:54,651
- [Marcus] Felix!
- [Lara] Stop!

282
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:57,279
- [gunshots]
- [Marcus] Felix!
